'''Augustina Stridsberg''', formerly '''Augustina Jirku''' (1892–1978),<ref>https://portal.dnb.de/opac.htm?method=showNextRecord&currentResultId=%22stridsberg%22%26any%26persons&currentPosition=1</ref> was an American citizen, and the mother of [[Margietta Voge]] (née Jirku). Both mother and daughter worked for [[NKVD|Soviet intelligence]] between 1943 and 1944. Stridsberg worked for the [[KGB]] San Francisco office. Her code name with Soviet intelligence, as deciphered by the [[Venona project]], was "Klara".<ref>[[John Earl Haynes]] and [[Harvey Klehr]], [https://books.google.com/books?id=nIYC5pd1XQoC&q=voge#v=snippet&q=Augustina&f=false ''Venona: Decoding Soviet Espionage in America'',] [[Yale University Press]] (1999), pgs. 369, 466. {{ISBN|0-300-08462-5}}</ref>
Stridsberg was also a writer and an [[interpreter]] as well as a literary translator.
