'''Paul E. Tracy''' is an American criminologist and professor at the [[University of Massachusetts Lowell]]. He is also the [[editor-in-chief]] of ''[[Crime & Delinquency]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://us.sagepub.com/en-us/nam/crime-delinquency/journal200959#editorial-board |title=Crime & Delinquency Editorial Board |website=us.sagepub.com |access-date=2017-07-20}}</ref> His research interests focus on [[juvenile delinquency]] and criminal careers.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.uml.edu/FAHSS/Criminal-Justice/faculty/Tracy-Paul.aspx |title=Paul Tracy |website=www.uml.edu |language=en |access-date=2017-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite press release |title=Dr. Paul E. Tracy Named Teacher of the Year  At The University of Texas at Dallas  |date=6 April 2004 |publisher=University of Texas at Dallas |url=http://www.utdallas.edu/news/archive/2004/drtracy.htm}}</ref> 
